<script type="module" src="./../controllers/home.js"></script>

<div class="container">

  <div class="rectangle" id="rectangle3">
    <span hidden id="league-name"></span>
    <span hidden id="league-id"></span>
    <span hidden id="round-no"></span>
    <div id="fixtures-info" class="table-container">
      {{> match-list-table}}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!--div class="rectangle" id="rectangle4">
    {{> rect-header title="Standings" link=standingsLink leagues=leagues selectedLeagues=selectedSLeague
    leaguepar="sleague" }}
    <div id="standings" class="table-container">
      {{> standings }}
    </div>

    <span style="grid-column: 1/4; padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px">Current Premier League standings,
      showing points, goal difference and recent form to help track qualification and elimination positions. Click on <a
        href="./league">MORE</a> for full league details, fixtures and historical performance. <br />Expected Points (xPts) estimate how many points a team deserved from a match based on performance rather than the final score.
We calculate xPts using expected goals (xG) and a Poisson probability model to estimate the likelihood of every possible scoreline. From these probabilities, we derive the chances of winning, drawing, or losing the match. Expected Points are then calculated as (win probability × 3) + (draw probability × 1), giving a more objective view of results over time and helping identify teams that are over- or under-performing.</span>
